                            The <strong>Tool #B1 Community Baseline Assessment</strong> is a qualitative, community-led evaluation deployed at the start of every humanitarian and development initiative. <strong>This Assessment is part of Meikswe Myanmar's Protection Mainstreaming Guideline.</strong> Its primary objective is to evaluate context-specific perceptions of safety, dignity, meaningful access, and local accountability, acting as a direct framework to guide the everyday practices of Meikswe Myanmar and other collaborating organizations' humanitarian and development workers.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                            Rather than evaluating minor isolated settlements in a piecemeal fashion, <strong>these assessments cover the whole township</strong>, mapping the entire administrative area to build comprehensive township-wide risk baselines. This strategic level of analysis ensures that our program delivery adaptations remain equitable, systematic, and thoroughly integrated with localized safety frameworks across all municipal and rural zones.
                        </p>
